  <prompt>
    Add xUnit tests proving the executor-config-schemas endpoint returns valid JSON with the expected
    shape. Per ADR-038, tests favor real integration over micro-mocks: the executor instances are real;
    only `IOpenAiClient` (and other heavy outbound dependencies) is mocked. The schema content itself
    is verified by serializing + asserting against expected JSON for at least the 5 priority executors.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET backend developer + test author. Honor ADR-038 KEEP-category patterns:
    integration-style endpoint test via WebApplicationFactory or test server; serialization assertions
    against the actual `JsonSerializerOptions` used by BFF; no banned `Mock&lt;HttpMessageHandler&gt;`,
    no DI-registration tests, no ctor null-check tests.
  </role>

  <goal>
    1. New test file `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Api/Ai/ExecutorConfigSchemasEndpointTests.cs` (or sibling location matching existing endpoint test layout)
    2. Test: endpoint returns 200 OK and a JSON object keyed by integer ExecutorType values
    3. Test: endpoint requires authentication (401 when no token)
    4. Test: response contains an entry for all 33 ExecutorType values (post-Wave-2 enum)
    5. Test: AiAnalysisNodeExecutor schema is non-empty and serializes with expected field names (camelCase per BFF convention)
    6. Test: AiCompletionNodeExecutor schema is non-empty and serializes with expected field names
    7. Test: ConditionNodeExecutor / EntityNameValidatorNodeExecutor / CreateNotificationNodeExecutor schemas are non-empty
    8. Test: a placeholder executor returns `{ fields: {} }` (or design-doc's exact empty shape)
    9. All tests pass; coverage report shows endpoint code touched
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="design-doc">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/spikes/getconfigschema-design.md</file>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="endpoint-impl">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/PlaybookBuilderEndpoints.cs (or sibling, per task 033)</file>
    <file purpose="schema-record">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/ExecutorConfigSchema.cs</file>
    <file purpose="existing-endpoint-tests">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Api/Ai/ — find sibling endpoint test pattern</file>
    <file purpose="test-architecture">docs/standards/TEST-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
    <file purpose="bff-constraints">.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-038">Testing Strategy — integration-heavy pyramid. KEEP-category test: endpoint integration via WebApplicationFactory; real executors (Singleton-registered) participate; only outbound deps (e.g., IOpenAiClient) mocked. BAN: Mock&lt;HttpMessageHandler&gt;, DI-registration tests, ctor null-check tests, "method-presence" tests.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI Minimalism — test setup uses real DI graph (WebApplicationFactory + ConfigureTestServices for the one mocked dep).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">BFF AI Architecture — tests validate the contract (route + payload shape), not implementation internals.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF Publish Hygiene — tests do not change publish artifact; verify at task 036.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §7 TEST-MODIFYING override">This task modifies tests/** — FULL rigor applies UNCONDITIONALLY (already declared via task tag). code-review + adr-check at Step 9.5 are MANDATORY.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10 test-update-obligation">Endpoints that map unconditionally MUST have unconditional service registration backing the test. Wave 3 endpoint maps unconditionally and executors are Singleton-registered unconditionally — no asymmetric-registration risk.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Pre-merge checklist applies. Placement decision: tests next to other endpoint tests under `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Api/Ai/`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="DO NOT TEST">Do NOT write tests that merely assert "GetConfigSchema method exists" or "DI registration calls AddSingleton" — these are banned scaffolding patterns per ADR-038 §7.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>ai/node-executor-authoring + testing</topic>
