    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL · 📋 REASON: TEST-MODIFYING override (task modifies tests/**, tag testing) — FULL rigor + Step 9.5 quality gates UNCONDITIONAL per CLAUDE.md §7 + ADR-038 · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md FR-16 + task 030 design doc + ADR-038 + `tests/CLAUDE.md` + `docs/standards/TEST-ARCHITECTURE.md`.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Verify dependency">
      Confirm task 033 shipped: endpoint exists; manually inspect the route registration.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Read existing endpoint test pattern">
      Find an existing endpoint test in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Api/Ai/` that uses WebApplicationFactory + ConfigureTestServices. Note the test base class / fixture used.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Create test file">
      Create `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Api/Ai/ExecutorConfigSchemasEndpointTests.cs` following the sibling pattern. Use the same WebApplicationFactory fixture.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Write tests in priority order">
      Add tests covering goal items 2-8 sequentially. Each test is named per pattern: `Endpoint_When_Then` (e.g., `GetExecutorConfigSchemas_WhenAuthenticated_Returns200`).
      For schema-content assertions: deserialize the response body, look up the integer key for ExecutorType.AiAnalysis (= 0), assert `Fields` is non-empty AND contains the expected field names from task 032's rich schema.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Mock IOpenAiClient if needed">
      The endpoint should NOT call IOpenAiClient (it only invokes `GetConfigSchema()` which is data-only).
      If the BFF startup wires IOpenAiClient with strict credentials, mock it via `ConfigureTestServices` to a no-op stub — this prevents test bootstrap failure.
      Do NOT mock INodeExecutor itself; use the real registrations.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Run tests">
      Run: dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~ExecutorConfigSchemasEndpoint"
      Goal: all tests pass.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Run full BFF test suite">
      Run: dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/
      Goal: no regression in the broader suite.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify acceptance">
      Open the test file; confirm tests cover goal items 2-8; confirm no banned patterns (no Mock&lt;HttpMessageHandler&gt;, no DI-reflection assertions, no method-presence reflection tests).
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality gates (FULL rigor — UNCONDITIONAL per TEST-MODIFYING override)">
      Run `/code-review` on the new test file. Run `/adr-check` against ADR-038 + ADR-010 + bff-extensions.md.
      Verify no ADR-038-banned patterns. Fix findings before commit.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 034 status complete; advance current-task.md to task 035.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Commit">
      Commit test file with conventional message.
      Example: test(bff/r7): xunit tests for executor-config-schemas endpoint (Wave 3 task 034, FR-16)
    </step>
  </steps>

